# --- SonarQube / coverage ---
# Kover XML lands under build/reports/kover/ (already covered above). The
# sonarqube Gradle plugin caches under .sonar/ and .scannerwork/. The
# scripts/sonar-export.ps1 helper dumps the issue/hotspot pulls to repo root.
.sonar/
.scannerwork/
sonar-issues.json
sonar-issues.csv
sonar-hotspots.json
sonar-hotspots.csv

# --- macOS / Windows / Linux noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# --- Editors ---
.vscode/
.fleet/

# --- Local secrets ---
# Carried over from the backend reference: never commit a real .env.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# --- Firebase ---
# google-services.json is per-project config (not strictly a secret, but
# standard practice to keep it out of the repo). Each contributor places
# their own copy at app/google-services.json after Firebase Console setup.
app/google-services.json
google-services.json

# --- AI assistant / agent scratch ---
.claude/
.aider*
.cursor/
.continue/

# --- Generated API artifacts ---
# Produced by scripts/gen-android-api-docs.py from the Retrofit
# interfaces under app/src/main/java/com/bughunter/core/network/api/.
# The Retrofit sources + the enterprise OpenAPI spec are the source of
# truth; these files are derivable from them. Regenerate locally with:
#     python scripts/gen-android-api-docs.py
docs/api/openapi.json
docs/api/openapi.yaml
docs/api/Bug-Hunter-Android.postman_collection.json
docs/api/android-api-usage.md
